# Vim Tips & Shortcuts

Set a word-wrap column break:

  :set tw=80

Show white-space characters:

  :set list
  :set nolist

Explore a folder:

  :Explore

or:

  :e .

Formatting a paragraph:

  gwip

Search and Replace string in the full file:

  :%s/search/replace/g

Repeat the * characters 17 times:

  17a*<Esc>

Duplicate a line to below/above:

   yyp/P

Select until end of line:

  v$

Show tab characters:

  :set list

Enter real tab character:

  On Windows / WSL:

     ctrl+q TAB


EOF
